The paper discusses the design of superconducting optoelectronic neurons for neural computing, which falls under the category of computational neuroscience (cs.NE). The use of optical communication and superconducting electronics also suggests potential relevance to the fields of optoelectronics (cs.ET), electromagnetics (cs.EM), and optical communication (cs.OC). Additionally, the use of waveguides and microscale devices suggests potential relevance to the field of circuit design (cs.CE).
